			<div class="content" id="post-content-3883877">
									

<p>For most of the article I was at a hesitant upvote until, near the end, I read</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It wasn't until later that she realized that he wasn't unbreakable. No one was. Sunny was just really, really good at hiding the cracks.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That's a fucking good line. And good writing as well. That's great humanizing and character development, and way better than the <em>upbeat while in bad situation</em> trope.</p>

