					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3938622&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205707" alt="The Great Hippo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3938622)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;" >The Great Hippo</a></span> <span class="odate time_1532428512 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Jul 2018 10:35</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3884101">
									

<p>Thank you; I appreciate you saying so! Part of my impetus for writing this series is that I've read a lot of stories with similar themes ('kids on the run from authority') that present it as a teenage power fantasy &#8212; living life on the run is a grand adventure that makes you strong and powerful.</p>
<p>I don't take issue with that theme, but for me, it's not a theme that correlates to reality. I'm writing this because I wanted to tell a story about a bunch of kids who become strong <em>despite</em> adversity, not <em>because</em> of it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
